item.title: Please help me. ive tried without asking for 3 days
item.dc:creator: @Mendorphins Mendorphins
item.description:
@Mendorphins wrote:

laurensman:

ummm if these are paired, then obviously theres an antileech lmfao.

What are you going on about? I wanted to know if the client and server he had came together, so that he wasn’t using a client that was incompatible with his server. This is not an anti leech. Anti leech is also against the rules and a waste of time. We’re an open source community for people to learn new things.

Sorry OP, I cannot help you any further. You’ve obviously getting nulled by the looks of things, what server do you have? Perhaps it is programmed poorly and needs a better anti null system.

If it’s old and poorly programmed, I’d recommend downloading a more up to date server. There’s some good ones out there.
